<title><p>How to start</p></title>
<p>FBReader looks for books in directories from <code>book path</code>. First of all you need to set this path. Go to options dialog (just click on <image l:href="#settings.png"/> in the toolbar) and change the value of <code>Book path</code> option in the <code>General</code> tab. This option must contain the list of directories containing <code>*.fb2</code> or <code>*.zip</code> files. Directories in the list are separated by colons.</p>
<p>Start <code>book choice dialog</code> (click on <image l:href="#books.png"/>), select a book from the list and read it.</p>
<p>To read <code>html</code> file, you need to add it to library. Start <code>add to library dialog</code> (<image l:href="#addbook.png"/>), select file and edit file information. Next time you can open this file using <code>book choice dialog</code> (<image l:href="#books.png"/>).</p>
